<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bleeds</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Bleed = Mez Immunity and as such is the enemy of a skald who can effectively use his mez in any situation.<br>
<br>
In the Evernight/Arctic Rift Combo, the bleed should be on Arctic Rift and not on Evernight.  As it stands now, I never use the rear styles because of this.  Sure the extra damage would be nice, but not nearly as useful as if I needed to mez my target and move to a different one or mezzing to flee/rest in a 1v1 situation.<br>
<br>
Also, there is currently no reason for a skald to spec to 50 axe.  With the Havoc/Tyr's Fury combo also causing a bleed, the bonus dmg does not outweigh having your target being mezzable.  If you plan on speccing 50 weapon, the choice is currently clear to use Sword.  IMO, Axe needs a solid stun available from one of the style chains other than the Block one.<br>
<br>
<br>
Axe in General (not related specifcally to Skalds) has another issue.<br>
<br>
--The cleave effect does not stack with the Pillager/Plunderer effect.  If you use your anytimes and then use cleave you get a &quot;Target Already Has This Effect&quot; message.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sideshow lvl50 ML3 Skald, Palomides <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A> at: 12/3/03 1:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=albron>Albron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/3/03 2:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tyrantsonline.com/albron.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Axe styles</span><hr size=1> Need a stun effect on one of our axe styles.  Of course as a 39 axe I would say Pillager/Plunder combo would be good for like a 6 sec stun instead of the hinder.  Being an anytime chain maybe thats too much though.  Another possibility is to get rid of bleed effect on Evernight, up its end useage and give the stun there.  However anything less than 5 secs is useless.  Other choice I can think of, and this maybe the best as other classes have side positional based med duration stuns, is put it on Glacial movement.<br>
