Ok style comments<br>
<br>
50 Skald here with 44 Sword (yes I no hammer and axe are reported better but I just like my sword)<br>
<br>
My basic issue is that most of the styles are just not ones I can or want to use.  I have a ton of bad choices.  In specific<br>
<br>
2- Whirling blade  -- Who is going to use a level 2 style in RvR??? Plus its high end<br>
4- Frost Cut --&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Never block so never use it<br>
6- Draw Out – Sad to say but this is my style of choice currently. Telling that the best style for us in the line is one we got 1 level after we became skalds<br>
8 - Northern Lights – Second most used style.  Solid but nothing special<br>
10 - Assault – Trade off on this and Draw out for general use.  Hits a little harder but hits lower to hit bonus<br>
12 - Temper – Ok for PvE but of no use for RvR.  Does the job though<br>
15 - Aurora – Chain off of Northern lights, again decent style, nice damage growth rate.  Should use it more often but have other things more important on my hot bar<br>
18 - Baldur’s Fury – Not worth the end cost for the damage or hindered effect<br>
21 - Reinforcement – “You parry” sure I do…  If you plan for this one you are an eternal optimist<br>
25 - Ice Storm – I miss the Old Ice Storm now its “you evade” again sure I do….<br>
29 - Rush – Chain off of reinforcement, If I cant parry how in the world will I ever follow up a parry style<br>
34 – Polar Rift – What can be said about a style that is higher end cost, same damage and lower hit bonus than a level 10 style<br>
39 – Niord’s Fury – chain from Frost cut.  No use to me.  Although I did get this off once on a mob just to see if I could<br>
44- Sif’s Revenge – Chain from Ice Storm, Again chain off of a event that almost never happens<br>
50 – Ragnarok – Great style, if you want to sacrifice lots of DD damage, highest damage add and any parry<br>
<br>
Ok sum it up.  15 styles, One I cant use due to spec choices, 6 from events that will almost never happen for a skald, 4 of little or no use in RvR since there is a better alternative, <br>
<br>
That leaves 4 all below level 15 (think about this, you could use /level 20 and get every sword style you would ever use)<br>
Assault - Ok but not special<br>
Draw out – One of choice<br>
Northern lights – best positional<br>
Aurora – only chain worth the time for me<br>
<br>
Some decent choices would be nice.  Raising Polar Rift so that it was actually an improvement on Assault would help.  Removing some of the block/evade/parry in favor for a stun style would also be appreciated.<br>
<br>
