<br>
To put it in simplified &quot;skald only&quot; terms:<br>
<br>
Sword for skalds is limited as:<br>
<br>
1) reactionaries are effectively useless to us.  Parry is our only viable defence, and a low one at that, and rush/reinforcement is not fantastic enough to displace other items on a skald's page 1 hotbar (as DDs and mez are far more of a priority).<br>
2) there is only one viable positional style (Northern Lights, side), because few skalds train all the way to 50 in a weapon.  If a rear style were available earlier on in sword growth, it would be far more popular.<br>
<br>
That being said, I like having a sword in my toon's hand <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=senjakvov>SenjakVoV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/6/03 6:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sword Styles</span><hr size=1> I am a Sword Skald, currently specced 46.46.10<br>
I have been sword for most of my 11 months, I went with Hammer for a while but went back to sword because :<br>
<br>
1. I seemed to be fighting mostly hibs, and I preferred to do slash damage instead of crush.  I remember the incident that tipped me back was missing a Conquer on a druid and losing, where I really thought that my sword would have done a better job.<br>
<br>
2. Swords are beautiful. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I would much rather see a sword in my hand than any other weapon.<br>
<br>
That being said, I would have to say that sword is the worst weapon for a skald to use, of the three we have available. So the only thing holding me to my sword is vanity. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Draw Out (level 6 taunt) has become my weapon of choice, it seems to be the only style I ever use nowadays, but I tend to use it to back up Reinforcement, which is the only other style I use now.  And I dont really like to do it, as Reinforcement has a bleed effect, which could really mess up my mez, but it is the only viable other style in my opinion, because it does great damage and has a good to hit bonus.<br>
<br>
Northern Lights - Aurora chain : The low to hit bonus on the opener bothers me, and the second just does not do good enough damage.  I was very surprised and disappointed when I realized that this chain was actually doing less damage than two draw outs.  I may be mistaken, I hope I am, but that is what it seems to me.<br>
<br>
Assault - Baldurs Fury : very high end cost, assault - ice storm used to be my bread and butter, this new anytime chain does not really hold a candle to it, though the snare effect is nice, I just cant rely on it.  And it does less damage than two draw outs.<br>
<br>
Ragnarok was a boon, I loved that style, though I would get VERY high variance on it, some days it would hit for less than my Assaults normally would do.  But, it was great to have a rear positional.  Sadly, I had to leave this style behind because 43 Battlesongs was just not enough, I left in favor of the 44 dd, 3 red resists and the greater damage add.<br>
<br>
My wish list for Sword includes : <br>
<br>
A medium to hit bonus to Northern Lights<br>
Increased growth rates on the side Chain, to make it better damage than any of my anytimes, which is only right for a positional chain.<br>
<br>
Remove the bleed effect on Reinforcement, or give us a second parry style that is comparable.<br>
<br>
Give us another Rear positionl style at 44 spec or less, this is the biggest thing I think.<br>
<br>
Except for the side style chain adjustments, I dont think these changes will help anyone BUT a skald, they seem to be just fine with most classes.  But Skalds need this love. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
